     Let us now briefly review the physical interpretation of the moments that will appear in our trade-off relation. In particular, the zeroth moment determines the rate of decoherence (and Lindbladian coupling more generally), the first moment gives the force exerted by the quantum system on the classical system, and the second moment determines the diffusion of the classical degrees of freedom. For this discussion, we shall take the classical degrees of freedom to live in a phase space




